<subSubSection id="C32478DFFFCCC20EFF78FDE16340FC91" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B812B54FFCCC20EFF78FDE16340FC91" blockId="11.[136,1452,585,929]" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis id="B94AF746FFCCC20EFF78FDE16113FDC5" bold="true" box="[136,289,585,611]" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">Diagnosis:—</emphasis>
Remarkable in producing bulbils at junction of petiole and leaf blade; most close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E50D7FFCCC20EFAE4FDE26224FD21" authority="K. Y. Guan &amp; D. K. Tian (2000: 132)" authorityName="K. Y. Guan &amp; D. K. Tian" authorityPageNumber="132" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longialata">
<emphasis id="B94AF746FFCCC20EFAE4FDE26599FDC5" box="[1300,1451,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">B. longialata</emphasis>
K.Y.Guan &amp; D.K.Tian (2000: 132)
</taxonomicName>
, differing in petiole 
<quantity id="4CC686B1FFCCC20EFD0FFDC46350FD21" box="[767,866,620,647]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" unit="cm" value="7.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.0">5–10 cm</quantity>
long, shallowly lobed leaf blade 
<quantity id="4CC686B1FFCCC20EFB2EFDC56572FD21" box="[1246,1344,621,647]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" unit="cm" value="10.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="8.0">8–12 cm</quantity>
long and wide and setose on both sides and margin, staminate flowers with pedicel 
<quantity id="4CC686B1FFCCC20EFC19FD386457FD0C" box="[1001,1125,656,682]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" unit="mm" value="17.0" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="12.0">12–22 mm</quantity>
long and tepals subequal in length, pistillate flowers with pedicel 
<quantity id="4CC686B1FFCCC20EFDC2FD1B629DFD68" box="[562,687,691,718]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" unit="cm" value="0.8" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="0.4">0.4–1.2 cm</quantity>
long and with 4 tepals, styles 
<quantity id="4CC686B1FFCCC20EFBF6FD1B644AFD68" box="[1030,1144,691,718]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" unit="mm" value="2.6" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.2">2.2–3 mm</quantity>
long. Also the new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E50D7FFCCC20EFEE1FD7F62A7FD56" authority="Irmscher (1951: 41)" authorityName="Irmscher" authorityPageNumber="41" authorityYear="1951" box="[273,661,726,753]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrotoma">
